PoE Scenario 1: IP Phone 
Â 
Network Design NoticeIP Phone deployment is a typical example for half-PoE application.Power Consumption Estimation: The IP Phone is a low-power device which does not consume too much currency. Normally, its power consumption is less than 7.5W, so, the half-PoE is good for the IP Phone deployment, and it saves money for customers. Cost-saving: Furthermore, the PoE technology saves the power adapter for each IP Phone, saves the power socket space, and reduces the wiring complexity, makes the desktop more clean and tidy. 
Â 
Bandwidth Calculation: By using the Z3526C2PL24W(24-Port FE with Half-PoE + 2GbE Uplink) as the PoE switch to connect the IP Phones, the bandwidth is big enough for each voice link, and the uplink is fast enough even all IP phones are in use. Management Features: In the web-based management features of the PoE switch, you can easily find a function to enable/disable each port. It makes the administrator easier to control each phone. He/she can even use the Remote Power Control feature of the PoE switch to control the power ON/OFF physically to each IP Phone.
Â 
Network Scalability: The IP Phones connect to PoE switches, and the PoE switches, in turn, connect to the central Gigabit switchdes, and then to the ISP. By using the 2-layer connection scheme, we can deploy hundreds or thousands of IP Phones. The structure is very scalable. Besides, The phone management can be converged to the same network management systems.
