PoE Scenario 2: IP CAM & Wireless AP 
Â 
Network Design NoticeIn hotels, dormitories or institutional buildings, there are some embeded service devices (such as wireless AP), security devices (such as IP Camera) or some IP devices of the Building Management System(for entrance control or fingerprint recognition). Network & Power Cabling Convergence: All of the devices and systems are gradually convergent into the IP infrastructure. These heterogeneous devices will benefit from connecting to the PoE switches. Both the IP traffic and the electric power are distributed by the same cabling systems. 
Â 
Cost-saving in lifecycle: It saves the set-up and installation costs, as well as the troubleshooting, maintenance, backup, and management-staff cost. It will be a great saving.No more power line wiring everywhere !Network Design: Should we connect different devices to different PoE switches or should we connect them to share the same PoE switch? It depends. If the network traffic for some devices is very critical, then we may suggest to use dedicated PoE switches for the critical devices.
Â 
Distance coverage consideration: The PoE switch can support the PoE devices within 100-meter radius. For large building or multi-building deployment, we should group the PoE devices into several areas, connecting the devices in the same area to the same PoE switch, and then connecting the PoE switches to the central switch.In some cases, the PoE switch will be in a few locations, far away from the central switch. The Z3624FL2P is a 24-port SFP & UTP Combo switch, with Layer 2+ management feature. By using the fiber switch as the central switch, we can easily connect all the PoE switches together.
