PoE Scenario 3: High-Wattage Devices 
Â 
New Standard: PoE+For some high power-consumption PoE devices, such as SpeedDome, a new standard, 802.3at (also known as PoE+), is finalized to provide more power to drive the devices.It may takes a while to get more popular about this standard because the PoE devices have to be redesigned to adapt to the new standard. 
Before configuring the PoE installation, you are suggested to check the electrical specification carefully, such as the volage, the currency, the power consumption, the pin-assignment, etc, to avoid any mismatch. 
